Executive Office - Resident Manager Beach Rotana
We are seeking for enthusiastic and committed individuals with exceptional communication skills that pride themselves on their ability to deliver extraordinary levels of service and provide creative solutions.
As a Resident Manager you are responsible to oversee and direct all aspects of the hotel operational departments and ensure these departments are well run by focusing on maximization of revenues and profits,
minimization of operating costs,
implementation and follow up of service standards and colleague development and thereby ensuring highest levels of guest satisfaction,
whereby your role will include key responsibilities such as:
• Support the overall strategic and day to day management of the property by establishing effective working relationships with department heads and senior colleagues
• Contribute to the design of the property’s business strategy
• Actively participate in the key management issues in the property e.g. capital projects,
refurbishment,
colleague development,
guest services,
etc.
• Actively support the sales department in the generation of revenue by ensuring the highest possible level of collaboration in the MICE sector to maximize yield and profit
• Work towards achieving the planned operational profit margins in both food & beverage and rooms
• Set objectives for each direct report,
conduct APR’s and review performance on a regular and consistent basis
• Assist in appointing,
developing and promoting an effective team of department heads and ensure that they are in turn built up trained,
competent and engaged colleagues
• Ensure the highest standards of quality in all aspects of the property operation,
guaranteeing that brand values and standards are never compromised
• Oversee the running of all departmental operations ensuring that departmental service standards are met consistently
Skills
Education,
Qualifications & Experiences
You should be holding a degree in hospitality management or a related field from an accredited college or university with previous experiences in the same role. A strong operational background,
either within the Rooms or Food & Beverage division is required and you must be a computer literate with effective and outstanding communication skills,
both verbal and written.
Knowledge & Competencies
The ideal candidate will be a leader who is naturally hands on,
with an on-site management style,
good relationship building skills and the ability to prioritize and make effective decisions. Ideally you are a dynamic and entrepreneurial manager who invigorates and motivates the operation with confidence and style while possessing following additional competencies:
Understanding the Business
Team Building
Planning for Business
Leading People
Valuing Diversity
Managing Operations
Customer Focus
Adaptability
Influencing Outcomes
Drive for Results
